citeinfo.title: Bike Paths Dane County, WI 2014

descript.abstract: This line data layer represents bike paths for Dane County and the City of Madison, Wisconsin in 2014. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Dane_BikePaths_2014.gdb. Other feature classes in this geodatabase include BCycle, BikeFacilities, BikeRoute, and FixedGuideWay. [Bike Paths and Trails: Generally crushed stone within rural areas; paved in urban areas. Includes most paths that can accommodate biking, but does not include all pedestrian paths.]
descript.purpose: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [Bicycle Path Inventory and Bicycle Plan.]
descript.supplinf: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements. For additional information, please see original license/data sharing agreement where applicable. The data for this layer was published with multiple feature classes, and the metadata was generated from the "Madison_City_BikePaths_2014" layer.
